prompt:
Create an educational medical cartoon panel in Dora the Explorer style (thick black outlines, flat colors, bright and friendly).

PANEL 29: One Week Follow-Up

SCENE: Clinic exam room, Elena showing legs to Dr. Erben

CHARACTERS:
- Dr. Young Erben: Petite Korean woman in her 40s, expressive rectangular glasses (#4A4A4A frames), warm smile, teal scrubs (#008B8B) or surgical greens (#2F4F4F), black hair in neat bun, professional yet approachable
- Elena Vasquez: 45-year-old Venezuelan woman, warm brown skin, shoulder-length dark curly hair, elementary school teacher, friendly expression, casual professional clothing

KEY VISUAL ELEMENTS:
- Healing incisions
- Reduced swelling
- Dr. Erben examining
- Positive progress

DIALOGUE/TEXT: Dr. Erben: 'Healing beautifully! How are your symptoms?'

EDUCATIONAL FOCUS: Early follow-up assessment

EMOTIONAL TONE: Positive progress

STYLE REQUIREMENTS:
- Dora the Explorer cartoon aesthetic: thick black outlines (3-4px), flat colors, no gradients
- Bright, welcoming, educational feel
- Clear, simple compositions
- Landscape orientation 1536x1024
- Medical accuracy with age-appropriate presentation
- Venezuelan cultural elements where appropriate

MEDICAL ACCURACY:
- Varicose veins: Twisted, enlarged, blue-purple superficial veins
- EVLA equipment: Modern laser generator, ultrasound machine
- Compression stockings: Gradient compression, knee-high
- Show procedure steps accurately but in cartoon style
